        "text_7ANXgn": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Mineral Oil Elimination System – Tackling Mineral Oil and Environmental Impact. Mineral oil leaks, fuel spills, and similar discharges present serious environmental risks when they enter wastewater systems. High-profile incidents like the Exxon Valdez oil spill highlight the scale of damage such contamination can cause to ecosystems and water sources.</p><p>To address these challenges, our team has developed a cutting-edge range of solutions designed to eliminate mineral oil contamination. Locations such as gas stations, which typically use oil/water interceptors, are ideal for these treatments. These closed-loop systems are more manageable to treat, improving wastewater quality and reducing the likelihood of violations or penalties from regulatory agencies.</p><p>By adopting a customized pretreatment plan from Environmental Biotech, your facility can proactively prevent discharge issues and avoid costly environmental fines.</p><p>Our latest innovation includes a specialized product line developed specifically for mineral oil removal: <a href=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/products/ecopure\" title=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/products/ecopure\"><strong>ECO PURE</strong></a> and <a href=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/products/ecopure\" title=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/products/ecopure\"><strong>SOIL GUARD</strong></a>—engineered to effectively eliminate mineral oils and support cleaner, safer wastewater management.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        },
